
                                                            *standard-input*


    VARIABLE
    *standard-input*  -  usual or default input stream

    DESCRIPTION
    Evaluating to an input stream that is used as the default for many input
    functions  (for example, read and read-char).  Input for the interactive
    top-level loop is normally taken from this stream.

    EXAMPLES
    Evaluating

    (cons 'a (read *standard-input*))

    with user input (b c d) returns (a b c d).

    SEE ALSO
    CLtL 21:327, *debug-io*, *error-output*, *query-io*, read, read-char,
    *standard-output*, streamp, *terminal-io*, *trace-output*












































